{"title_page": "Todor Todoroski", "text_new": "{{short description|Macedonian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                 = Todor Todoroski\n| image                =\n| fullname             =\n| birth_date           = {{Birth date and age|1999|02|26|df=y}}\n| birth_place          = [[Prilep]], [[North Macedonia]]\n| height               = 1.80 m\n| currentclub          = [[NK Osijek]]\n| clubnumber           = 27\n| position             = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]]\n| youthyears1  = {{0|0000}}\u20132012 | youthclubs1 = [[FK 11 Oktomvri|11 Oktomvri]]\n| youthyears2  = 2013\u20132014       | youthclubs2 = [[FK Ko\u017euf|Kozhuf]]\n| youthyears3  = 2014\u20132016       | youthclubs3 = [[FK Metalurg Skopje|Metalurg]]\n| youthyears4  = 2016\u20132017       | youthclubs4 = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]]\n| years1   = 2016      | clubs1 = [[FK Metalurg Skopje|Metalurg]] | caps1 =  3 | goals1 = 0\n| years2   = 2017\u20132018 | clubs2 = [[FK Vardar|Vardar]]            | caps2 = 41 | goals2 = 0\n| years3   = 2019      | clubs3 = [[NK Osijek|Osijek II]]         | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 1\n| years4   = 2019\u2013     | clubs4 = [[NK Osijek|Osijek]]            | caps4 =  2 | goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2014\u20132015\n| nationalteam1 = [[North Macedonia national under-17 football team|North Macedonia U17]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2016\u20132017\n| nationalteam2 = [[North Macedonia national under-19 football team|North Macedonia U19]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 12\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2018\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[North Macedonia national under-21 football team|North Macedonia U21]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 12\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| pcupdate = {{date|2019-10-28}}\n| ntupdate = {{date|2019-10-28}}\n}}\n\n'''Todor Todoroski''' ({{lang-mk|\u0422\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440 \u0422\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0438}}; born 26 February 1999) is a [[North Macedonia|Macedonian]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[NK Osijek]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]].\n\n==Playing career==\nTodoroski made his senior football debut on 20 April 2016 at the age of 17, by entering the game for [[FK Metalurg Skopje|Metalurg]] at the start of the second halftime in the [[First Macedonian Football League]] match against [[FK Renova|Renova]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/1-mfl-2016-abstieg-fk-renova-metalurg-skopje/|title='1 MFL 2016 Abstieg Renova Metalurg Skopje'|website=www.worldfootball.net|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> That season he went on to play two more games, which eventually brought him a transfer to [[FK Vardar]] in the following summer in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/todor-todoroski/mkd-1-mfl-2016-abstieg/metalurg-skopje/3/|title='Todor Todoroski: 1 MFL 2016 Abstieg - Metalurg Skopje'|website=www.worldfootball.net|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> Vardar initially signed him for their youth team, but in 2017 they eventually promoted him to the first team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/todor-todoroski/mkd-1-mfl-2016-2017/vardar-skopje/3/|title='Todor Todoroski: 1 mfl 2016-2017 - Vardar Skopje'|website=www.worldfootball.net|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://old.ekipa.mk/todoroski-da-go-nosish-dresot-na-vardar-neprotsenlivo-chuvstvo/|title='\u0422\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0438: \u0414\u0430 \u0433\u043e \u043d\u043e\u0441\u0438\u0448 \u0434\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043e\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0412\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0430\u0440 \u2013 \u043d\u0435\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0446\u0435\u043d\u043b\u0438\u0432\u043e \u0447\u0443\u0432\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e'|website=www.ekipa.mk|language=mk|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> Todor was regular in the upcoming [[2017\u201318 Macedonian First Football League|2017\u201318]] and [[2018\u201319 Macedonian First Football League|2018\u201319]] seasons, which cought the eye of Croatian side [[NK Osijek]] who decided to sign him at the beginning of 2019 to play for their second team.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nk-osijek.hr/vijesti/18141/nova-lica-u-osjeckim-redovima/|title='Nova lica u Osjeckim redovima'|website=www.nk-osijek.hr|language=hr|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref> After successful 6 months playing for Osijek II in the [[Croatian Second Football League]], in the summer of 2019 they decided to promote him to the first team. On 28 July 2019, he made his debut for the first [[NK Osijek|Osijek]] team, having played the full game against [[NK Gorica|Gorica]] in the second round of the [[2019\u201320 Croatian First Football League]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/todor-todoroski/cro-1-hnl-2019-2020/nk-osijek/3/|title='Todor Todoroski: CRO 1 HNL 2019-2020 - NK Osijek'|website=www.worldfootball.net|language=en|access-date=2019-07-27}}</ref>\n\n===International career===\nEver since 2014 Todoroski has been regular at most of North Macedonia's national youth teams.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{WorldFootball.net|todor-todoroski}}\n* {{Soccerway|todor-todoroski/387441}}\n\n{{NK Osijek squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Todoroski, Todor}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Prilep]]\n[[Category:Macedonian footballers]]\n[[Category:North Macedonia international footballers]]\n[[Category:North Macedonia youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:FK Vardar players]]\n[[Category:NK Osijek players]]\n[[Category:Macedonian First Football League players]]\n\n\n{{RMacedonia-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Macedonian footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                 = Todor Todoroski\n| image                =\n| fullname             =\n| birth_date           = {{Birth date and age|1999|02|26|df=y}}\n| birth